      "question_number": 1,
      "question_text": "Two categorical variables are associated if:",
      "attempted": 2,
      "data_i18n": null,
      "options": [
        {
          "text": "The conditional distributions differ across categories",
          "is_correct": true,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "They have the same frequencies",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "The marginal frequencies are equal",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "The grand total is large",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "If conditional distributions differ noticeably, there is an association between the variables. Two categorical variables have an association if the distribution of one variable differs across categories of the other. The other options — 'They have the same frequencies', 'The marginal frequencies are equal', and 'The grand total is large' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
    },
